***XPATH*******

why do we need XPath locators
developers may not have provided other locators in the html
by using xpath we can identify those web element easily

what is an xpath ?

Xpath is just a query language that help you to identify element

Types of Xpath
1) Absolute xpath
--> starts with a starting node in html
is starts with a single slash


2) Relative xpath
// tagname[@attribute='attribute value']
Example
//input[@type='password']
hey can u fins me the tag
find me tag nem , with atribute and atribute value atribute value


Absolute xpath how it works e,g

<html>
<head>
</head>
<body>
<div>
<a>dajfk<a>
</div>
<div>
<img> </img>
</div>
</body>
</html>


2 inspecting using text

//tagname[text()='text']

3 identify by using conti=ain method
//tagname[contains(@attribute,'attribute value')]

Example
<itagname class="form",id=form0'>
//tagname{contains(@id,'form')]

<input class="form",id=form">
//input [contains(@id,'form')]

4 identify using starts-with method
will identify the elements with the starting partial value

//tagname[starts-with(@attribute,'partial starting value')]

//tagname[starts-with(text(),'partial starting value')]


........Topic advance Xpath........

Advanced Xpath is based upone parent child sibling ancestor relationship

1 Identifying elemnt using following sibling
//tagname[@attribute='attribute value']/following-sibling::tagname
go to the tagname whose has attribute with value 'attribute value'now get me the following sibling of this tag
// input[@id='message']/following-sibling::lable
go to the tagname input which has the attribute id with value message now get me its following sibling with
tagname label

in order to use this advanced path(following sibling we need to identfy one sibling that can be
identified uniquely)





